 To make the arrow heads shorter (less elongated) in TikZ, you need to adjust both the `length` and possibly the `width` parameters in your arrow tip specification. Here's how to modify your command with shorter arrow heads:

```latex
\newcommand{\threedaxes}[6][0.8]{%
    % #1 = scale (optional, default 0.8)
    % #2 = i-axis label
    % #3 = i-axis length
    % #4 = j-axis label
    % #5 = j-axis length
    % #6 = k-axis direction (1 for out, -1 for in)
    \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=#1]
        % Define axis style with shorter arrow tips
        \tikzset{axis/.style={-{Latex[length=1mm, width=1mm]}, thick}}

        % i and j axes
        \draw[axis] (0,0) -- (#2,0) node[right] {\footnotesize $#3$};
        \draw[axis] (0,0) -- (0,#4) node[above] {\footnotesize $#5$};

        % Draw a white-filled circle first to cover the axis lines
        \fill[white] (0,0) circle (0.12);
        % k axis 
        \draw[thick] (0,0) circle (0.1);
        \ifnum#6<0
            % Into of page (cross)
            \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (0.07,0.07);
            \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (-0.07,-0.07);
            \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (0.07,-0.07);
            \draw[thick] (0,0) -- (-0.07,0.07);
            \node at (-0.2,-0.2) {\footnotesize $k$};
        \else
            % Out of page (dot)
            \fill[black] (0,0) circle (0.03);
            \node at (-0.2,-0.2) {\footnotesize $k$};
        \fi
    \end{tikzpicture}%
}
```

I've reduced the `length` parameter from 2mm to 1mm to make the arrow heads shorter. You could try even smaller values like 0.8mm if needed.

Alternatively, you could try a different arrow head style that is naturally shorter:

```latex
\tikzset{axis/.style={-{Stealth[length=1mm, width=1mm]}, thick}}
```

The `Stealth` arrow style is typically more compact than the default `Latex` style.

If you want even more compact arrow heads, you could try:

```latex
\tikzset{axis/.style={-{Triangle[length=0.8mm, width=1mm]}, thick}}
```

The key parameters to adjust for shorter arrow heads are:
- Reduce the `length` parameter (makes the arrow tip shorter)
- Maintain or slightly increase the `width` parameter (keeps the arrow tip visible)

